    {
      "text": "A 46-year-old man presents for routine follow-up. He has no diagnosed medical problems and takes no prescribed medications. His main concern at this visit is a history of chronic right nasal congestion for many years. He reports that he is unable to move air through the right naris, but breathing through the left naris is satisfactory. He also reports intermittent anterior nosebleeds from the right naris in the winter. He has tried nasal strips without improvement.\nWhat is the most likely cause of this patient's presentation?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Intranasal use of illicit drugs"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Use of topical nasal decongestants"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Sinus infection"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Nasal septal deviation"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Allergies"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Intranasal use of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nF07i3&anker=Ze484aa13dc518fe96d58522a9f0446ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"nF07i3\" data-anker=\"Ze484aa13dc518fe96d58522a9f0446ba\" data-section-id=\"2tWT1M0\" data-sememe-id=\"V5bGQ8\">cocaine</a> can result in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a50Qig&anker=Zc6fb5dc19b631aa8df6c96c74dbe4a73\" data-learningcard-id=\"a50Qig\" data-anker=\"Zc6fb5dc19b631aa8df6c96c74dbe4a73\" data-section-id=\"O1WIS40\" data-sememe-id=\"MEbMwv\">nasal septal perforation</a> and irritation, but unilateral obstruction would be unlikely.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The <span data-sememe-id=\"Ze1Zxf0\">mucosal</span> inflammation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mq0V_S&anker=Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-learningcard-id=\"mq0V_S\" data-anker=\"Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-sememe-id=\"21aTTj\">allergic rhinitis</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-section-id=\"R4YlQ6\" data-sememe-id=\"Y1an2j\">chronic rhinosinusitis</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vj0AXT&anker=Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-learningcard-id=\"vj0AXT\" data-anker=\"Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-section-id=\"OtXId-\" data-sememe-id=\"d-Yow7\">rhinitis medicamentosa</a> (a condition induced by overuse of <span data-sememe-id=\"_1b5js\">nasal decongestants</span>) is usually bilateral.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>The <span data-sememe-id=\"Ze1Zxf0\">mucosal</span> inflammation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mq0V_S&anker=Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-learningcard-id=\"mq0V_S\" data-anker=\"Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-sememe-id=\"21aTTj\">allergic rhinitis</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-section-id=\"R4YlQ6\" data-sememe-id=\"Y1an2j\">chronic rhinosinusitis</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vj0AXT&anker=Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-learningcard-id=\"vj0AXT\" data-anker=\"Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-section-id=\"OtXId-\" data-sememe-id=\"d-Yow7\">rhinitis medicamentosa</a> (a condition induced by overuse of <span data-sememe-id=\"_1b5js\">nasal decongestants</span>) is usually bilateral.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ru0fs3&anker=Zc9e171b812992625c75344234c09e92a\" data-learningcard-id=\"ru0fs3\" data-anker=\"Zc9e171b812992625c75344234c09e92a\" data-sememe-id=\"JjbsYF\">Nasal septal deviation</a> is among the most common causes of unilateral nasal obstruction. It often stems from congenital abnormalities or from trauma that has deformed the <span data-sememe-id=\"WT2PpSa\">midline</span> nasal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7o04WS&anker=Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-learningcard-id=\"7o04WS\" data-anker=\"Zde961151d845714430b6e0600d08840e\" data-sememe-id=\"TJb6tu\">cartilage</a> and obstructed nasal airflow.<br><br>The <span data-sememe-id=\"Ze1Zxf0\">mucosal</span> inflammation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mq0V_S&anker=Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-learningcard-id=\"mq0V_S\" data-anker=\"Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-sememe-id=\"21aTTj\">allergic rhinitis</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-section-id=\"R4YlQ6\" data-sememe-id=\"Y1an2j\">chronic rhinosinusitis</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vj0AXT&anker=Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-learningcard-id=\"vj0AXT\" data-anker=\"Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-section-id=\"OtXId-\" data-sememe-id=\"d-Yow7\">rhinitis medicamentosa</a> (a condition induced by overuse of <span data-sememe-id=\"_1b5js\">nasal decongestants</span>) is usually bilateral. Whether <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ru0fs3&anker=Zc9e171b812992625c75344234c09e92a\" data-learningcard-id=\"ru0fs3\" data-anker=\"Zc9e171b812992625c75344234c09e92a\" data-sememe-id=\"JjbsYF\">nasal septal deviation</a> predisposes a patient to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-section-id=\"R4YlQ6\" data-sememe-id=\"Y1an2j\">chronic sinusitis</a> is controversial.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The most common cause of unilateral nasal obstruction is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ru0fs3&anker=Zc9e171b812992625c75344234c09e92a\" data-learningcard-id=\"ru0fs3\" data-anker=\"Zc9e171b812992625c75344234c09e92a\" data-sememe-id=\"JjbsYF\">nasal septal deviation</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>The <span data-sememe-id=\"Ze1Zxf0\">mucosal</span> inflammation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mq0V_S&anker=Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-learningcard-id=\"mq0V_S\" data-anker=\"Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-sememe-id=\"21aTTj\">allergic rhinitis</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z737ce892784d975993302436e68fb4f1\" data-section-id=\"R4YlQ6\" data-sememe-id=\"Y1an2j\">chronic rhinosinusitis</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vj0AXT&anker=Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-learningcard-id=\"vj0AXT\" data-anker=\"Z685ffa2b505566ee96625ca0e48697bb\" data-section-id=\"OtXId-\" data-sememe-id=\"d-Yow7\">rhinitis medicamentosa</a> (a condition induced by overuse of <span data-sememe-id=\"_1b5js\">nasal decongestants</span>) is usually bilateral.</div>",
